'''David Tomblin ('''[[October 18]], [[1930s#1930|1930]] - [[July 20]], [[2005]]) was the first assistant director on [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']]<ref name="ESB">{{Film|V}}</ref> and [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']]. 
==Biography==
[[File:DavidTomblin.jpg|thumb|left|196x196px|Carrie Fisher and David Tomblin]]
He also wrote and directed [[Warwick Davis]]' short film ''[[Return of the Ewok]]'' during production on ''Return of the Jedi'' in [[1982]]. In this film, he starred as the voice of [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] and [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] over actor [[David Prowse|Jeremy Bulloch]].

